## 5.1 Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Question 1 (3 Marks)  
**[KTU University Exam – Dec 2023, PECPT755]**

> Define a `Mapper` class in the Java MapReduce API. List its type parameters and explain the role of the `Context` object.

#### Model Answer (3 Marks):

A **Mapper** in Java MapReduce is an abstract base class `org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper` that the user extends to define the transformation logic of the Map phase. Its four type parameters are:

$$
\text{Mapper}\langle \text{KEYIN}, \text{VALUEIN}, \text{KEYOUT}, \text{VALUEOUT} \rangle
$$

representing the types of the input key, input value, intermediate (emitted) key, and intermediate (emitted) value respectively.

The **`Context` object** passed to `setup()`, `map()`, and `cleanup()` is the **communication channel** between the user's Mapper and the Hadoop framework. It allows the mapper to:

- Emit intermediate pairs via `context.write(K, V)`.
- Update Hadoop `Counter`s via `context.getCounter()`.
- Signal progress via `context.progress()` to prevent speculative kill.
- Read job configuration via `context.getConfiguration()`.

*(Examiner's note: 1 mark definition, 1 mark type parameters, 1 mark Context — fits KTU 3-mark pattern.)*

