## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Marks-Loss Pitfalls in Java MapReduce Questions (KTU 2024):**
>
> 1. **Forgetting `setJarByClass()`** — Without this, the cluster cannot ship your JAR. **−2 marks** in Driver questions.
> 2. **Confusing `setOutputKeyClass()` with `setMapOutputKeyClass()`** — When map and reduce output types differ, you MUST use both. **−1 mark**.
> 3. **Using `int`/`String` instead of `IntWritable`/`Text`** — Hadoop's serialization framework does NOT support raw Java primitives as map output types. **−2 marks** if the code won't compile.
> 4. **Defining the combiner as the mean** — Combiners MUST be commutative and associative. Mean is neither. **−1 mark** in theory questions.
> 5. **Putting logic in `main()` instead of in the Mapper/Reducer** — This defeats the entire purpose of MapReduce parallelism. **−2 to −3 marks** if the code structure is wrong.
> 6. **Re-allocating output objects inside the loop** — Performance is fine for small data, but examiners may flag it as poor practice. Use `private final static` constants.
> 7. **Calling `outputPath.exists()` check** — HDFS output paths MUST NOT pre-exist; `FileOutputFormat` will throw an error if they do. **−1 mark**.

