## 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- ✅ **Three mandatory classes:** Mapper, Reducer, Driver.
- ✅ **Mapper** extends `Mapper<KEYIN, VALUEIN, KEYOUT, VALUEOUT>`; overrides `setup()`, `map()`, `cleanup()`.
- ✅ **Reducer** extends `Reducer<KEYIN, VALUEIN, KEYOUT, VALUEOUT>`; overrides `setup()`, `reduce()`, `cleanup()`.
- ✅ **Driver** uses `Configuration`, `Job`, `FileInputFormat`, `FileOutputFormat`.
- ✅ **Type parameters** may differ across map and reduce; use `setMapOutputKeyClass` / `setOutputKeyClass` accordingly.
- ✅ **Hadoop Writable types:** `Text`, `IntWritable`, `LongWritable`, `FloatWritable`, `DoubleWritable`, `NullWritable`.
- ✅ **Keys must implement `WritableComparable`** for sorting and partitioning.
- ✅ **Combiner** = local reducer; must be **commutative and associative**.
- ✅ **Partitioner** = `HashPartitioner` by default; routes by `hashCode() mod R`.
- ✅ **Number of mappers** ≈ number of input splits = $\lceil \text{input size} / \text{split size} \rceil$.
- ✅ **Default split size** = 128 MB (= HDFS block size).
- ✅ **Compilation & submission commands:** `javac`, `jar -cvf`, `hadoop jar <jar> <DriverClass> <in> <out>`.
- ✅ **Output file naming:** `part-r-XXXXX` (one per reducer).
- ✅ **Configuration properties** (KTU-favorite): `mapreduce.job.reduces`, `mapreduce.map.output.compress`, etc.
- ✅ **Optimization tricks:** static final `IntWritable one`, `Text.set()` reuse, combiner usage, compression of map output.
- ✅ **DistributedCache** ships read-only files to all nodes via `job.addCacheFile()`.
- ✅ **Counters** are enums extending `Enum`; use `context.getCounter()`.
- ✅ **Combiners NOT valid** for: mean, median, unique-count, set union.
- ✅ **Combiners VALID** for: sum, max, min, count, product.
